		<div>I thought SW:G Cantinas and Med Centres were a good idea, just poorly implemented.  <br />
<br />
It really needed to be something that was encouraged rather than forced on people - players usually resent having play-styles forced on them.<br />
<br />
If there was an optional, short-term benefit gained from watching dancers or being patched by a doctor, people might have been a lot more open to it.<br />
<br />
Classes like entertainer or image designer might have been better as a collection of secondary skills, rather than an entire profession.</div>
