		<div>It's an interesting idea, but i really don't like the idea of penalizing people for their style of gameplay.  I usually go all out for 2-4 hours, then i log off.  I pick quests i can do in that time then once they are finished, i get to choose to try another, go watch the trade channel in Elwynn Forest, or log off.<br />
<br />
I think the basic design of the game which includes the myriad of quests provides suitable &quot;resting&quot; points already, which people use to travel, sell goods, stock up on food/drink, and look for another group or something.  The need to add some forced resting time isn't that apparent to me.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		<!-- sig -->
			<div>
				__________________<br />
				<div align="center"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=88222" target="_blank">~ Telegareth Sugarbritches - Arcanist ~</a></div> <div align="center"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=88204" target="_blank">~ Amberlee Sugarpants - Overlady ~</a> </div>
<div align="center"><a href="http://www.legacyofsteel.net" target="_blank">~ Legacy of Steel ~</a></div>
			</div>
