	<div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px">Quote:</div>
	<table cellpadding="6" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%">
	<tr>
		<td class="alt2" style="border:1px inset">
			
				Forcing people to take a break (though it's not really forcing, since if there was a penalty it would be very small) is not a bad thing. Quite the contrary actually. It's called MMO- fatigue, and it's a very real problem for some people that just don't know how to stop. I think people really underestimate the stress they put their bodies through when they do leveling sessions like that. I myself have never and will never do something like that, but I know people that have. It's pretty unhealthy. I'm glad they're concerned about the welfare of their players and I really think you need to give it a chance and see it through. 
			
		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>
</div>This is so true, and what's worse is if you are really immersed you may not even realize how long you have been sitting in front of the screen, how long you have been ~alert~ in combat.  It may be simulated, but it still has an effect on your body, and it's a good thing to encourage (not force if the penalty is small) people to take a break, relax, enjoy the world and other people's company.  Go make a sandwich!  If you are anti-social or just want to keep going you still can.  Chances are by the time an xp penalty kicked in you'd have stuff to sell anyway and might as well take the break.  It also cycles people out of areas so one group doesn't monopolize an area for 10 hours.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
